      {
        "key": "2021011423300766000_2020.07.15.20154401v1.36",
        "unstructured": "Assuming a simplified scenario in which a constant proportion of the total population is vaccinated weekly, the proportion of the population that is not vaccinated U can be modeled to decrease exponentially in time as U (t) = exp(\u2212\u03c5t). Consequently, in order to achieve 27% vaccination coverage after an 8 month (or 34.7 week) period (i.e. U (34.7) = 0.73), a weekly vaccination rate of 0.91% of the remaining unvaccinated population would be required."
      },
